  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "CPI data came in as expected at 3.3% with core remaining subdued, triggering a risk-on move that pushed Bitcoin above $73K and weakened the dollar. However, consumer sentiment collapsed to 47.6 vs 52.0 expected with inflation expectations spiking to 4.8% (1-year) and 3.4% (5-year), creating a concerning divergence between market euphoria and consumer reality. Manufacturing data remains weak with factory orders flat and durable goods declining, suggesting underlying economic fragility persists.",
    "regimeImpact": "The relief rally continues but consumer sentiment collapse and rising inflation expectations suggest this could be a classic bear market rally trap before the next leg down.",
